sentences: George Wassouf (Arabic: جورج وسوف; born 23 December 1961, nicknamed Abou-Wadie (ابو وديع) and Sultan El-Tarab (سلطان الطرب))
In a career spanning more than four decades, he has released more than 30 albums.
He was discovered by his first manager and producer George Yazbeck at a wedding party that Wassouf was performing at, aged 12 years old.
He became famous after appearing on the Lebanese show Studio El Fan 1980 when he was 19 years old as Sultan of Tarab.
